        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 3:50PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 349 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Marion, or near Old Fort, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marion, Old Fort, Lake James State Park, Lake James, Nebo, Sugar
Hill, Pleasant Gardens, Glenwood, Fero, and Dysartsville.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
